Chilean Stocks: Colbun, CTI, Forus and Sigdo Koppers

-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 
2011-08-19T20:53:28Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-19/chilean-stocks-colbun-cti-forus-and-sigdo-koppers.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Chilean trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4:12 p.m. New York time.  The Ipsa index fell 0.5 percent to 4,129.71.  Colbun SA (COLBUN)   retreated 0.2 percent to 118.98
pesos, its second day of losses. Chile’s third-largest power
generator posted a net loss of $16.1 million in the second
quarter, down from a profit of $55.5 million a year earlier,
according to a filing sent today to regulators.  CTI Cia. Tecno Industrial SA (CTI CC) rose 6 percent to
34.99 pesos, its fourth day of gains. Swedish home appliances
producer Electrolux AB confirmed it’s in talks with Chilean
holding company  Sigdo Koppers SA (SK)  to buy CTI, a Chilean producer
of home appliances.  Sigdo Koppers SA (SK CC) fell 1.9 percent to 800.2 pesos,
its second day of losses.  Forus SA (FORUS)   rose 5.3 percent to 1,400 pesos, the
biggest gain in a week. The operator of apparel and footwear
stores posted second-quarter profit of 7.3 billion pesos ($15.6
million), up 77 percent from a year earlier, according to a
filing sent yesterday to regulators.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduardo Thomson in Santiago at 
